<br>
The cleric in a small guild that's made a lot of friends used to be able to put his ass in SolB and let his friends know to be ready for the call.  This cleric could put out this call and have a reasonable amount of time for his &quot;pickup&quot; forces to array.  <br>
<br>
Now, you need to have the backing of a completely uber force to complete your epic.  They must have the required 20-25 level 60s on at the time that RF pops or else some other guild that does (the required &quot;uber guild&quot;) will take it.  Its no longer up to the work of the cleric doing the quest...its up to the guild to provide full support for that cleric at the time that RF pops.<br>
<br>
There's no one to complain to but Verant.  Everyone that's posted against lists and for &quot;the one that has the forces gets the mob&quot; is completely right...but that doesn't make it suck any less.  Again, the game, like RL, makes it much easier for those that already have to gain more.<br>
<br>
<br>
Then again, I'm just a level 53 newb in a midbie guild that doesn't know anything.  Go about your business and ignore me. <p><br>
